    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "23229f5a_12a175af",
        "filename": "src/sksl/SkSLIRGenerator.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 3
      },
      "lineNbr": 605,
      "author": {
        "id": 5085
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-11-27T16:00:52Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "This would be a fun one to debug. :) Would it be simple enough to disallow return in vertex shaders?",
      "revId": "e5244f15bbab2ecac5b43b5824920fe0f20cd451",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "ce9f380d_0a489484",
        "filename": "src/sksl/SkSLIRGenerator.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 3
      },
      "lineNbr": 605,
      "author": {
        "id": 5633
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-11-27T16:14:02Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I agree it would be hard to debug, but the problem isn\u0027t just here. I think a return almost anywhere in sksl will break everything- vertex or fragment. (I actually use returns sometimes for debugging..) Also this particular limitation has always existed for the normalization that used to happen in Ganesh.\n\nDo you think we need to work out a more general solution for returns, all throughout sksl?",
      "parentUuid": "23229f5a_12a175af",
      "revId": "e5244f15bbab2ecac5b43b5824920fe0f20cd451",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "53b29973_ee515cbd",
        "filename": "src/sksl/SkSLIRGenerator.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 3
      },
      "lineNbr": 605,
      "author": {
        "id": 5085
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-11-27T16:48:03Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Yep it\u0027s always been possible to return and escape the transformation ever since we were emitting GLSL straight to the driver\u0027s compiler. As we\u0027re making SKSL a \"real\" language and moving the translation from sksl\u0027isms to glsl/spirv from the builder code and into the compiler we have the opportunity to make things work more consistently and close some holes.\n\nWe don\u0027t have to solve this in this CL but it seems to me that we should strive to make it so that sksl can have a clear definition of sk_FragCoord that doesn\u0027t depend on whether there was a return. If we don\u0027t require return in our shaders then a simple to implement solution could be there is no return in the language (until we find a need for it). If that\u0027s not a simple solution then I\u0027d be happy to push closing this hole out into the future.",
      "parentUuid": "ce9f380d_0a489484",
      "revId": "e5244f15bbab2ecac5b43b5824920fe0f20cd451",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "2f1a5f64_10bd38c1",
        "filename": "src/sksl/SkSLIRGenerator.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 3
      },
      "lineNbr": 605,
      "author": {
        "id": 5640
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-11-27T16:51:04Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I agree we should close the hole; I felt dirty writing that comment but wasn\u0027t sure how much work it was worth to fix it. It shouldn\u0027t be *that* bad to fix for real, let me take a swing at it.\n\nChris, if you run into other issues like this with return breaking things, please let me know. It shouldn\u0027t be doing that.",
      "parentUuid": "53b29973_ee515cbd",
      "revId": "e5244f15bbab2ecac5b43b5824920fe0f20cd451",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "dd1e1cc2_bb5b381d",
        "filename": "src/sksl/SkSLIRGenerator.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 3
      },
      "lineNbr": 605,
      "author": {
        "id": 5633
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-11-27T17:08:51Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Agreed. I think disallowing return in a vertex shader sounds like a good solution, as long as we can still return in a fragment shader.\n\nReturning from a geometry shader is no problem, since the transform should just be injected whenever they call EmitVertex().\n\nRE: other issues with return, I was mostly referring to when an FP calls return - then sk_FragColor doesn\u0027t get set. In a GP you can actually set sk_FragColor and then return to skip your FPs (which I actually like for debugging purposes).",
      "parentUuid": "2f1a5f64_10bd38c1",
      "revId": "e5244f15bbab2ecac5b43b5824920fe0f20cd451",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "f6676fdb_2379a839",
        "filename": "src/sksl/SkSLIRGenerator.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 3
      },
      "lineNbr": 729,
      "author": {
        "id": 5633
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-11-27T17:08:51Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "How does this work for geometry shaders? (Where the vertex shader outputs device-space coords and the geometry shader normalizes them?)\n\nIn that case the transform should be injected every time they call EmitVertex().",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 729,
        "startChar": 12,
        "endLine": 729,
        "endChar": 33
      },
      "revId": "e5244f15bbab2ecac5b43b5824920fe0f20cd451",
